cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.CR, cs.SI 

The paper deals with physical layer security in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The use of coalitional games to model the cooperation problem suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the game theory (cs.GT) community. Additionally, the paper addresses security concerns (cs.CR) and proposes a distributed algorithm for self-organization (cs.SI) in wireless networks.
